 <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">About 52% of the participants got health care services from government facilities that includes 10% services received from village-level community clinics (
  <a ref-type="fig" rid="F0001" href="#F0001">Fig. 1</a>). A substantial number of households got the service from unqualified providers, either village doctors (33%) or local drug stores (12%). About 65% of households were nearby (2 km radius) to remote rural government health care settings such as community clinics (28.5%) and union health centre (36.5%) (
  <a ref-type="fig" rid="F0002" href="#F0002">Fig. 2</a>).
 </p>
